{
  "stem": "23428.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Really, the only nightmarish thing that I remember from the prison is when they were opening the cell door and three SS men came in and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] claimed that somebody had written a newspaper article hoping that the-- that the-- the street of one of the major avenues in Budapest called Andrassy was-- was going to be plastered with the heads of SS people.",
      "word_count": 71
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was probably purely imaginary, I imagine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "These guys were dreaming.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyway, so they came in and said, who wrote that?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, since obvious nobody wrote that, they picked on the-- on the most Jewish-looking guy in the crowd, who happened to be a-- a printer-- I'm sure he had nothing to do otherwise with journalism, he was nothing but a printer-- and nearly beat him to death in front of all of us, his blood flowing and all that.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'll never forget his ears.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were like-- like balls when it was finished.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was done in the cell itself?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was done in the cell, with 20, 25 people standing at attention.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, easily.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, it was not bigger than this room, probably smaller.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was very crowded.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So you know, having not-- having had not a lot seen physical trauma before, this was a terrible day, which I'll never forget.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then, the only other change from routine was, of course, there was a lot of fear about being called out, because people always felt that when they were called out, they were put in the courtyard and shot.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and everybody was sort of ready for that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, from the end of July until September, so that makes it August-- about six weeks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
